item, look at where it drops and who it's intended for, and adjust accordingly.<br>
<br>
For Instance<br>
<br>
Lockjaw Hide Vest--Lockjaw-- level 25ish.  this is a bit high for the focus 1 effect on the item, though lockjaw could be done by a full group of 18's or so--untwinked and lucky.  At least its one of the few focuses you can get at the appropriate level to use.<br>
<br>
Batskull Earring-- Oowomp and other Ogres in W.Karana-- level 35ish-- has a focus 1 effect.  Innappropriate for the mob entirely.  If a &lt;20 can't get it in a group, the item needs improved, or the mobs need lowered, or the item needs moved.  Preferably, I'd like to see focus 1 dropping off &lt;15 at the very highest, so you actually get use from them for a little while.<br>
<br>
Robe of the Oracle--The Oracle of K'Arnon-- level 40.  Why o' why is there an Imp Damage 1 effect on this?  It should be 2 at least, or the Oracle needs severly gimped.  It would take an decent raid force of level 20's to bring her down. <p><br>
