<br>
I think that some issues need to be considered before they attempt to rebalance the low level game; it's not the same as it was 4 years ago.  I bet it's pretty difficult for a true newbie to find a group these days unless you're in a popular zone like Paludal Caverns, so newbies are pretty much left to soloing or grouping with 1 or 2 others (usually alts).  A group of 3 untwinked newbies is not going to stand much of a chance at progressing through the game at the target level.<br>
<br>
High level buffs are what make gaining exp at the low levels bearable.  A lot of people play low level alts because it's fun to twink the hell out of them and go destroy the mobs that gave you grief when they were leveling your main char.  Another reason to play a low level alt is boredom with the slow progression of a high level character.  If it's gonna be a pain in the ass to progress your level 20 character too, why bother?  And if there aren't any high level characters playing low level alts, who are the true newbies going to group with?  It's not a very good way to market your game to new customers.  Sure, it was fine 4 years ago when the newbie zones were full of players searching for a group, but it's different now.<br>
<br>
The game is pretty much focused on 55+ characters now.  The prime goal is to get 55+ so you can enjoy new content.  Why make it more difficult for new customers? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79710">Ealadan Azurefire</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
