<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=beltalek>Beltalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 12:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OMG</span><hr size=1> <br>
I'd have to agree that something needs to be done with the group buff bug.  And it obviously is a bug and not what was intended.  As usual it sounds like Sony is going with the &quot;swat a fly with a sledgehammer&quot; approach, though.<br>
<br>
Many buffs have varying levels of benefit based on the caster's level.  If they would instead make this dependent on the RECIPIENT'S level I think it would provide a more balanced answer to the problem.  For example, KEI bestows 14 mana/tick (amongst other things).  If this were changed to recipient level / 4 (max 14) then the buff would still have benefit to many players, but would not be unbalancing.  For the single-digit twinkmongers, the spell would have little more effect that breeze (again, only considering mana regen).  On a 20th, they'd get 5/tick.. Less that C1 I believe., at 40 it is 10/tick.  <br>
<br>
The actual formulae isn't what I want to focus on... My point is that they don't have to implement an &quot;all or nothing&quot; solution.  They will, because it is probably the easiest to code, but they don't have to.<br>
