<br>
My main is a level 60 gnome warrior, and I often spend an extremely frustrating 2+ hours sitting in Tranquility looking for a group. This is the prime reason why I created my dark elf Wizard, now level 36. I created him so that I could get away from the life of my downtime-filled warrior, and play something that didn't rely on sitting for hours waiting on a group.<br>
<br>
KEI enabled me to do just that - I could hop on my wizard, grab a KEI, and just go to town having fun. It was a relief from the grind and boredom of my main character. But now, without KEI, playing my wizard is like playing him as if he were my main character, if only for a few more levels. I also have a 25 mage and 21 necro that I use for alts, too, and playing those will become more of a chore, with more downtime.<br>
<br>
And that's what it comes down to, in reality. Downtime is the key issue - what KEI does, for the most part, is reduces downtime. And reduced/eliminated downtime is what I want when I play my alts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zigonzagoff>ZigonZagoff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/03 11:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OMG</span><hr size=1> The other annoying thing about KEI is everyone <br>
