Zigon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/24/03 3:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hacking &amp; stuffs</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You have to also consider the availability of the item, not just where it drops. Batskull earrings, oracle robes, these are things which sell for pennies or are given away or even destroyed on my server, they are so common and basically worthless.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
I have to strongly disagree.<br>
<br>
I don't care how often it drops.  Level appropriate gear should drop off of level appropriate mobs.  The level 1 focus effect clearly means that the item is intended for the &lt;20 crowd, especially anything with Damage 1 on it, as everyone that can cast has a DD of some kind, at pretty regular levels. <br>
<br>
That an item intended for &lt;20 level characters drops off of 35+ mobs is stupid crazy.  It's also very Verant.  <br>
<br>
On this particular issue, the focus effects, I think level 1 focus should be questable from your guildmaster within 10 levels of handing in your newbie note.  Level 2+ foci can be a bit more rare, but should still be obtainable by level 40 at least, with level 3 foci appearing on items of low stats around 51 or 52. <p><br>
