<br>
SOE should instead make limits on all facets of a characters abilities, scaled by level, from 1 to 45 (the point where they can receive any buffs). Every character would have a maximum weapon damage rating (already in the game, but needs to be refined and expanded), a minimum weapon delay, a maximum mana regen capability, maximum stats, etc, etc, etc. <br>
<br>
This would effectively limit twinking and high level buffing, without doing away with them altogether. People could still get some of the benefits of twinking without becoming gods in the newbie garden.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valeerxev>ValeerXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/03 8:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hacking &amp; stuffs</span><hr size=1> I want to play EQ with my friends.<br>
