</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jwiz1>jwiz1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/03 9:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> grouping at lower levels?</span><hr size=1> I play some alts, like many of us.  But has everyone who is commenting in this thread really, and I mean REALLY, tried to play alts and group?  If sony is going to stop (slow down) the twinking - I'm in favor of that - but they (and some of the posters here) have to realize that the game has CHANGED.  It's not like it was 3, even 2, years ago.  Just go to COM and try to get a group.  Go into Mistmoor.  Go to Paw - hell - go anywhere in the older zones - almost always empty, unless a quest item is in there.  And guess what - if you need to go there to get a quest item?  You are screwed unless you bring your own group, unless you can solo.  So, yeah, it's twinking, but if the game requires you to solo more at lower levels (unless you are in one of the newer popular zones, like paludal, etc) - is it really twinking?  <br>
<br>
While I'm on the subject, I think Sony needs to step back and look at player/zone density.  It's wonderful that they are adding new zones, but if the server can't support more and more players, then of course, by definition, zones are going to have less and less people in them.  With POP and LOY, who would want to go back to original zones any more?  <br>
<br>
So, I think it's a more complicated issue than just saying &quot;twinking is bad&quot;.  Yes - it's absurd to have KEI on a low level caster - clearly not what was intended, but, it did make it fun when I was forced to solo (or didn't feel like grouping with my alt).<br>
<br>
Jwiz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soulcraver>Soulcraver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/03 10:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> buffs</span><hr size=1> Well having started up a new twinkie and not having the ability to play for hours on end, when this goes live a couple of things needs to be changed.<br>
<br>
1. Change the fizzle rate.  (You might have all forgot but you can fizzle away your entire mana bar easily without getting any skill ups, and then be sitting on your ass until you can cast again.  That is no fun and detracts from game play immensely.  And in fact doesn't make any sense that a level 4 casting level 1 spells would fizzle away like they do.<br>
<br>
2. Increase mana regeneration rate somewhat.  This is akin to stamina regen for melee.  If you've never played a melee try it and see the difference between recouping mana and recouping stamina.<br>
<br>
Lastly, remember that most new players are not &quot;New&quot;.  They are re-rolled players.  People like me who have a level 65 main, 2 level 52's and are still looking for &quot;new love&quot; (at least until WoW comes out. /wink).  Having to go through all those low levels again without any boost will definitely kill the motivation for people like me.  I don't mind the thought of &quot;recommended&quot; levels on many items with increasing returns as you gain.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, I won't be leveling any new characters after this goes through and I'm sure many others won't either given the increased time it will take to level up now.  Maybe that's good maybe that's bad but my prediction is that it will invariablely hurt SOE in the pocket sooner than later. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26620.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26620.topic&start=41&stop=47>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=26620.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=26620.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=26620.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=26620.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26620.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26620.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20